e changing role of knowledge and the clergy in thirteenth-century Iberia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311049093008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Pilot 2016z978311066595608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019z978311065878108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017z978311060680540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442621817423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442621817.jpg  a978-3-11-049093-0  UTP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-060680-5  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017c2016d2017  a978-3-11-065878-1  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019c2014d2019  a978-3-11-066595-6  UTP eBook-Package Pilot 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG